#PressPlay: Get y’all popcorn ready, Chance the Rapper’s new movie drops today in theaters across the country! “Chance the Rapper’s Magnificent Coloring World” marks the first time an artist has independently distributed a film to theatres.
________
“Magnificent Coloring World” is a concert film self-distributed through Chance the Rapper’s House of Kicks production company and film house.
________
Chance wrote, produced, edited and starred in the film, working hard this past year to bring never-before-seen footage to his fans. The footage was filmed in 2017 right before Chance took home 3 Grammys for his critically acclaimed mixtape “Coloring Book.”
________
Fans will be able to see the film in person for a limited time in several cities including Los Angeles, New York, Chicago, Detori, Las Vegas and Philly.

node.title: Chance The Rapper’s Film Released Today

Whew! #Roommates, if you’ve had a few complaints about this summer’s weather, you’re not alone! According to @npr, the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) has shared new data that shows last month was “the hottest month ever recorded in human history.”
______________________________
“In this case, first place is the worst place to be," NOAA Administrator Rick Spinrad said in a statement. "July is typically the world's warmest month of the year, but July 2021 outdid itself as the hottest July and month ever recorded."
______________________________
Humans have been recording weather changes for the last 142 years. The 20th-century average land and ocean-surface temperature was reportedly 60.4 degrees, however last month it was up by 1.67 degrees. This is the third year in a row since 2019 that the record has been broken. 
______________________________
The Pacific Northwest is experiencing another heat wave with temperatures rising above 100 degrees. Some temperatures are contributing to wildfires in Oregon and California. Rick of the NOAA says we’re on a “disturbing and disruptive path” due to climate change. Thoughts, #Roomies?
